-- Bernanke makes no remarks on economic outlook
-- 
-- Fri Dec 1, 2006 9:18am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/12/01/businesspro-usa-fed-bernanke-dc-idUSWAT00666620061201

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - Federal Reserve Chairman Ben 
Bernanke did not discuss the economy or the outlook for 
inflation or interest rates on Friday in brief introductory 
remarks at a conference on monetary policy. 

  Federal Reserve Vice Chairman Donald Kohn is due to speak 
at the conference at around 8 p.m. (0100 GMT) on "Uncertainty, 
Monetary Policy and Communication." Kohn is scheduled to take 
questions from the audience after his remarks.  European Central Bank Vice Chairman Lucas Papademos at 
1:15p.m. (1815 GMT) addresses a luncheon at the conference, 
which is organized in part by the Federal Reserve and the ECB.